h3. Summary

When an already logged in non-sysadmin user tries to access a restricted servlet, the {{response.sendtRedirect(loginUriProvider.getLoginUriForRole(URI.create("plugins/servlet/<app-servelet-url>"), UserRole.SYSADMIN));}} results in an infinite redirect loop. If the user is not logged in, then the redirect works fine.

Sample code restriction:
{code:java}
if (userManager.isSystemAdmin(userManager.getRemoteUserKey())) {
    response.setContentType("text/html;charset=utf-8");
    response.getWriter().write("<html><head><title>Test</title></head><body>Hello World!</body></html>");
}

else {
    URI uri = URI.create(URL);
    final String redirectUrl = loginUriProvider.getLoginUriForRole(uri, UserRole.SYSADMIN).toString();
    response.sendRedirect(redirectUrl);

    //OR

    response.sendtRedirect(loginUriProvider.getLoginUriForRole(URI.create("plugins/servlet/<app-servelet-url>"), UserRole.SYSADMIN));
}
{code}

h3. Summary
The Documentation for [Increasing JIRA application memory | https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiraserver/increasing-jira-application-memory-938847654.html] does not display steps for jira 7.0 and above

h3. Currently states:
For JIRA 5.1 or below:
{code}
tomcat6w //ES//%SERVICENAME%
{code}
For JIRA 5.2 or above:
{code}
tomcat7w //ES//%SERVICENAME%
{code}

h3. Missing:
For JIRA 7.0 or above:
{code}
 tomcat8w //ES//%SERVICENAME%
{code}

 
h3. Notes
Document versions for 7.0 - 7.4 reflect the correct information

Also For Version specific documentation, a list of commands for older versions is not relevent

h3. Summary

Incorrect autoCompleteUrl for Assignee in createmeta REST API call

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Run the following GET REST call in Jira:
{code}
"/rest/api/2/issue/createmeta?projectKeys= SSP&expand=projects.issuetypes.fields
{code}
(i) where SSP should be replaced by the Project Key

h3. Expected Results
The autocomplete provides a rest call for the assignable users for that project:
{code}
"assignee": {
"required": false,
"schema": {
"type": "user",
"system": "assignee"
},
"name": "Assignee",
"key": "assignee",
"autoCompleteUrl": "https://instance.net/rest/api/latest/user/assignable/search?project=SSP&query=",
"hasDefaultValue": false,
"operations": [
"set"
]
}
{code}


h3. Actual Results
The Autocomplete URL is incorrect:
{code}
"assignee": {
"required": false,
"schema": {
"type": "user",
"system": "assignee"
},
"name": "Assignee",
"autoCompleteUrl": "http://instance.com/rest/api/latest/user/assignable/search?issueKey=null&username=",
"hasDefaultValue": false,
"operations": [
"set"
]
}
{code}
 
h3. Notes
This returns correctly in Jira Cloud. 

h3.Workaround

Use the REST call:
{code}
GET /rest/api/2/user/assignable/search
{code}
to find the assignable user for that project/issue. For more info: https://docs.atlassian.com/software/jira/docs/api/REST/7.12.0/#api/2/user-findAssignableUsers

